It has taken a few phone calls and time so really disappointed. I have given a 3 because the company customer care were as helpful as they could be under the circumstances. Please remember to cancel your eDreams Prime subscription within 15 days!
The way eDreams handles this subscription is extremely misleading and reflects a bad business strategy approach.

I was charged for the eDreams Prime subscription without giving clear consent after the trial period ended. When I contacted customer service, they were trying to refuse to issue a refund and instead offered a ¬£90 voucher, which is completely unacceptable.

Under the UK Consumer Contracts (Information, Cancellation and Additional Charges) Regulations 2013, customers have the right to cancel within 14 days of renewal and receive a full refund. eDreams should respect this legal right and treat customers fairly.

Offering vouchers instead of refunds and making the cancellation process unclear damages trust and discourages repeat customers. This is a very poor business practice and shows a short-sighted approach to customer relationships.

I strongly recommend others to avoid signing up for eDreams Prime unless you intend to use it long-term ‚Äî and even then, read the fine print carefully.

Bought Hisense fridge freezer from AO, first day the ice maker or water dispenser didn't work, rang Hisense and they sent out a repair person. They said they would have to order parts. After 10 weeks and numerous phone calls we was told the parts can't be found and a repair eta could not be given. Went back to hisense and they said the policy is to wait for parts and could not issue refund until parts eta was confirmed. We was told we had to just wait for parts which is unacceptable. As we had not involved AO at this point we went back to them as we had bought it through them and within 10 minutes they had got onto hisense and got them to issue refund, we obviously didn't get another hisense. Would never buy there products again. Poor poor customer service

I visited the Clacton on Sea branch with my mother in law on Monday 13th October.
We were looking for several things and found them all quickly and easily with the help of Kathy and Katie, who were both friendly and knowledgeable.
The store itself was so clean, tidy and well laid out that we actually found it a pleasure to shop there! üôÇ
Also, having never shopped in the store for myself before because the clothes felt too old for me, I was pleasantly surprised to find several things I liked. I bought a beautiful dress and will definitely be back on my own to purchase more items.

Quick transaction and delivery of 1 package but unfortunately I never received the 2nd part and as DHL have failed to deliver. I have asked for the delivered package to be collected as it is of no use to me and a refund to my credit card which I am still waiting for. It has taken a few phone calls and time so really disappointed. I have given a 3 because the company customer care were as helpful as they could be under the circumstances. All the pain due to a courier company failing its duty to do what it is paid to do.

I found it impossible to book the event I wanted to redeem my voucher against. The only option was to pay for another voucher. When I had booked my experience, and paid ¬£92 for afternoon tea and Christmas light trail at Port Lympne animal park, I was notified by the park that the price doesn't include entrance fees, and I'll have to pay a further ¬£70 for our admission. There's no way of speaking to someone at buyagift to get help with a booking, and the FAQ page didn't cover my question. Very disappointed

‚≠ê Extremely Frustrating Refund Experience

I‚Äôve been waiting OVER 4 MONTHS for my refund and still haven‚Äôt received it. Qatar Airways confirmed they‚Äôve already sent the funds to Aunty Betty, yet the team keeps giving conflicting information and NO clear updates. The lack of communication and accountability is unacceptable. Please process my refund immediately ‚Äî this has taken far too long. I am struggling to afford to live without my money now post travels!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

Absolutely shocking customer service! Parcel never arrived, advised it had been taken to local pick up point. Went to collect it the next day and was advised they don‚Äôt have it! I‚Äôve emailed asos 5 times now and they just state ‚ÄòI can see our carrier have your parcel and it will be delivered today‚Äô 6 days later and nothing! Cannot speak to anyone but AI Chat! Will never shop with ASOS again!

Worst customer service and account team. They are holding my transfer for last 5 days, accounts review team asked for documents and information which were being provided and since then silence. No one is responding and answering to emails. They are holding my funds for no reason neither it was a big transfer or first transfer. Don‚Äôt use this service if you need an urgent transfer.

In three (or was it only two?) phone rings, I was on the phone to a human being who personally, professionally, took my case in charge, kindly answered all the lengthy questions I could have to come back with an appropriate solution for a slightly uncommon insurance requirement. Thank you, Jessica, thank you also for following-up on all this.

My Kobra 3 does not have a warranty and was constantly throwing a very unique error. Obi had the answer and could have sold me a very expensive motherboard but instead, sent me the way to apply a simple fix and Voila, works like brand new! Another very complete and fast service from Anycubic Support!
